title: Introduction to C Programming
des: C is a general-purpose, procedural computer programming language supporting structured programming, lexical variable scope, and recursion, with a static type system.

title: Introduction to Algorithms
des: Algorithms are step-by-step instructions for solving problems efficiently, fundamental in computer science for tasks like sorting, searching, and optimization.

title: Introduction to C++ for DSA
des: C++ for DSA (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a versatile programming language used to implement efficient algorithms and data structures.

title: Basic Data Structures
des: Basic data structures like arrays, linked lists, and stacks are fundamental tools in computer science for organizing and managing data efficiently.

title: Introduction to OOP Python
des: Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) in Python involves creating reusable objects and classes to model real-world entities, enhancing code modularity and maintainability.

title: Software Engineering
des: Software Engineering is a systematic approach to design, develop, test, and maintain software systems, focusing on quality, efficiency, and reliability.

title: AWS, Cloud Computing
des: AWS (Amazon Web Services) is a leading cloud computing platform offering a wide range of scalable and on-demand cloud services for businesses.

title: Database (MySQL)
des: MySQL is an open-source relational database management system, widely used for storing and managing structured data in various applications.

title: Problem-Solving Part
des: Problem-solving is a critical skill involving analyzing, devising strategies, and implementing solutions to address complex issues effectively and efficiently.
